WEBVTT

00:05.306 --> 00:06.305
SAM: <i> Previously on</i> Aquarius...

00:06.307 --> 00:08.941
HALPERT: <i> You got naughty</i>
<i> photos of somebody in</i>
<i> the White House?</i>

00:08.943 --> 00:11.110
That'd be illegal. I'm a cop.

00:11.112 --> 00:12.511
(GRUNTING)

00:12.513 --> 00:15.581
GRACE: <i> Sam, my daughter,</i>
<i> Emma, she's gone.</i>

00:15.583 --> 00:16.181
<i> Get my little girl back.</i>

00:16.183 --> 00:18.684
KEN: <i> Obviously, finding her</i>
<i> is the important thing,</i>

00:18.686 --> 00:19.618
<i> but if you can keep it quiet,</i>

00:19.620 --> 00:20.953
<i> there are people</i>
<i> who'd appreciate it.</i>

00:20.955 --> 00:22.588
SAM: <i> If I'm gonna</i>
<i> find this girl,</i>

00:22.590 --> 00:23.989
<i> I need a cop in that world.</i>

00:23.991 --> 00:25.257
-I report to you?
-Yep.

00:25.259 --> 00:27.559
CHARLIE: Emma,
you survive with us.

00:27.561 --> 00:28.460
I'm Charlie Manson.

00:28.462 --> 00:30.796
I'm not the only
one Manson can hurt.

00:30.798 --> 00:32.431
We can't afford this, Kenny.

00:32.433 --> 00:33.565
<i> Me and your daddy.</i>

00:33.567 --> 00:34.767
<i> I would never have chose that,</i>

00:34.769 --> 00:35.367
<i> but it led me to you.</i>

00:35.369 --> 00:38.404
GUAPO: This'll be the
first shipment through
Nippon warehouse.

00:38.406 --> 00:40.706
Delivery's tomorrow at noon.

00:40.775 --> 00:41.740
Where's the stuff?

00:41.742 --> 00:43.075
Now I know I can trust you.

00:43.077 --> 00:45.144
-You're a real cop?
-Last I checked.

00:45.146 --> 00:46.745
ROY: <i> If she's looking</i>
<i> for Charlie,</i>

00:46.747 --> 00:48.280
<i> she's got to go through me.</i>

00:48.282 --> 00:49.982
I plow them all eventually.

00:49.984 --> 00:50.949
ROY: Sugar clam.

00:50.951 --> 00:52.251
What are you doing here?

00:52.253 --> 00:52.684
Charmain!

00:52.686 --> 00:55.187
KEN: <i> This cop and Grace,</i>
<i> that's the problem.</i>

00:55.189 --> 00:56.655
GRACE: <i> I'm sick of lying</i>

00:56.657 --> 00:58.023
<i> about what I am,</i>

00:58.025 --> 00:59.224
<i> who I love.</i>

00:59.226 --> 01:00.292
No, Kenny.

01:00.294 --> 01:01.660
Buddy, you can't...

01:01.662 --> 01:02.528
-(SCREAMS)
-(GUNSHOTS)

01:02.530 --> 01:06.598
We will lead
the world to a brand-new age.

01:38.199 --> 01:39.998
(MUSIC PLAYING SOFTLY)

01:55.850 --> 01:57.616
(EMMA SHUDDERING)

02:13.934 --> 02:16.502
(CLATTERING)

02:49.837 --> 02:51.303
Breathe, Emma.

02:51.305 --> 02:53.105
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

02:53.440 --> 02:57.509
That feeling in your skin,
that tingling,

02:57.511 --> 03:00.479
that's us stepping
into a new world.

03:00.948 --> 03:02.314
(INHALES DEEPLY)

03:05.219 --> 03:08.554
Put this somewhere, anywhere.

03:09.123 --> 03:11.123
No sense makes sense.

03:13.694 --> 03:17.062
-No, not this. I can't.
-Shh. Hey, hey!

03:17.364 --> 03:18.263
Hey.

03:18.265 --> 03:22.234
The three of us,
it's our time now.

03:22.836 --> 03:26.171
There can be no
birth without...

03:30.244 --> 03:31.677
Come on.

03:33.581 --> 03:35.047
Come on!

03:35.115 --> 03:38.917
There can be no
birth without...

03:40.888 --> 03:42.554
(STUTTERING) Death.

03:43.657 --> 03:45.290
Attagirl.

04:04.645 --> 04:06.511
(SNIFFLING)

04:29.737 --> 04:33.405
(SOBBING)

04:55.663 --> 04:58.196
MAN: <i> Both suspects had to die.</i>

04:59.466 --> 05:01.333
SAM: <i> I wanted him to</i>
<i> get shot by whoever</i>

05:01.335 --> 05:03.135
<i> was in that house</i>
<i> if they were armed</i>

05:03.137 --> 05:05.937
<i> because I didn't</i>
<i> want us to get shot.</i>

05:06.307 --> 05:08.740
-MAN: And the brother?
-(MAN 2 GROANING)

05:10.344 --> 05:12.377
No, he didn't have to die.

05:13.347 --> 05:15.447
I wanted him to die.

05:18.419 --> 05:21.186
MAN: <i> You will be</i>
<i> receiving the Medal of Valor</i>

05:21.188 --> 05:23.689
<i> to the cheers of</i>
<i> a grateful city.</i>

05:23.691 --> 05:26.191
<i> In Los Angeles,</i>
<i> we close killings.</i>

05:26.193 --> 05:29.294
<i> You closed these for good.</i>

05:29.563 --> 05:32.230
Detective, I'm Ron Kellaher.
I'm with Internal Affairs.

05:32.232 --> 05:36.768
There was a witness, so
I'm gonna need to
speak to you tomorrow.

05:49.183 --> 05:50.282
You had no idea.

05:50.284 --> 05:53.185
Medal of Valor,
Internal Affairs, cameras.

05:53.187 --> 05:56.388
It all seems
a tad orchestrated,
don't you think?

05:56.390 --> 05:57.589
If you think I
had anything to do

05:57.591 --> 05:58.857
with that,
we can just step outside.

05:58.859 --> 06:03.228
Relax, Cut.
This is not
a John Wayne movie.

06:07.167 --> 06:10.001
Look at this.
Everybody's doing the funny.

06:10.003 --> 06:12.504
Whoa. Yeah. Again, innocent.

06:13.040 --> 06:14.873
What's in it?

06:18.278 --> 06:18.710
Fan mail.

06:18.712 --> 06:22.614
Now that's what
I'm talking about,
the upside of fame.

06:22.616 --> 06:24.883
Is there a number on there?

06:25.886 --> 06:27.953
CUT: Anonymous.

06:27.955 --> 06:32.124
Playing hard to get. Me likey.

06:33.827 --> 06:35.193
Sam.

06:35.462 --> 06:36.661
It was absolutely Roy.

06:36.663 --> 06:38.096
You hear
anybody else with him?

06:38.098 --> 06:39.398
-I don't think so.
-Good.

06:39.400 --> 06:42.868
One-man motorcycle kidnapping
strikes me as unlikely.

06:42.870 --> 06:45.437
I'm guessing she just
had to be friendly-like.

06:45.439 --> 06:47.639
-Make him feel comfortable.
-Great.

06:47.641 --> 06:48.940
You know where
these guys hang out?

06:48.942 --> 06:51.410
The gang's got a clubhouse.
I've never been,

06:51.412 --> 06:53.111
but it's
called the Bleu Room.

06:53.113 --> 06:54.246
Which one?

06:54.248 --> 06:54.813
How many are there?

06:54.815 --> 06:59.484
Santa Monica,
Van Nuys, Burbank,
Hollywood, that I know of.

06:59.620 --> 07:00.986
So what do we do?

07:00.988 --> 07:02.721
It's called police work.

07:24.945 --> 07:27.379
-(RATTLING)
-(MUFFLED GROANING)

07:46.166 --> 07:49.601
(PANTING)

08:57.738 --> 08:59.504
(GROANING)

09:10.250 --> 09:12.150
WOMAN: Oh, my God, is he okay?

09:12.152 --> 09:15.820
MAN: Mister? Mister?
You all right?

09:16.757 --> 09:17.789
Get over here.

09:17.791 --> 09:19.291
WOMAN: What do we do?

09:49.423 --> 09:52.290
So, your uncle died. Uncle...

09:52.292 --> 09:54.559
Ted. I told you.

09:54.561 --> 09:57.963
See, we kind of know
the owner of
the funeral parlor,

09:57.965 --> 10:01.466
and he was not at all happy
about being woken up for this.

10:01.468 --> 10:06.071
There ain't no dead Ted
nowhere on the premises.

10:08.141 --> 10:13.411
So, you sure
you don't want
to try a little?

10:14.047 --> 10:16.181
It focuses the mind.

10:29.229 --> 10:30.729
-(BABY FUSSES)
-What's wrong?

10:30.731 --> 10:32.664
Nothing at all, Cherry Pop.

10:32.666 --> 10:37.202
We all have past karma.
I'm not exempt.

10:37.204 --> 10:38.136
RALPH: Charlie!

10:38.138 --> 10:39.804
You watch over Valentine.

10:39.806 --> 10:42.474
Take him to the cellar.
Lock the door.

10:42.476 --> 10:44.609
-What? But, Charlie...
-Shh!

10:44.611 --> 10:46.544
No, no, no. See, now,

10:46.546 --> 10:50.515
it is our destiny
to reach the stars.

10:50.517 --> 10:53.218
No power on earth
can change that.

10:54.321 --> 10:56.921
What, Charlie? What?

11:02.596 --> 11:06.731
RALPH: What the hell, Charlie?
Ain't nothing in the cupboard?

11:07.134 --> 11:08.500
I came a long way.

11:08.502 --> 11:10.135
CHARLIE: Sorry, my man.

11:10.137 --> 11:12.771
Lot of mouths to
feed around here.

11:12.773 --> 11:14.673
Sometimes,
the cupboard gets bare.

11:14.675 --> 11:19.511
You should have told
me you were coming.
I'd have been good and ready.

11:19.813 --> 11:21.680
Now, you know me, Charlie.

11:23.850 --> 11:28.119
Sometimes, I don't even know
what I'm gonna do
my damn self.

11:29.489 --> 11:32.090
That pretty little
thing back there,

11:33.026 --> 11:36.494
why don't you tell
her to drop the knife

11:36.963 --> 11:39.497
and go fetch me
something to eat?

11:41.868 --> 11:43.301
Charlie.

11:43.503 --> 11:45.303
Do like he says, Sadie.

12:14.367 --> 12:17.569
Okay,
here's the thing, I lied.

12:19.172 --> 12:22.073
You lied about what exactly?

12:22.075 --> 12:26.811
I was sent there to do a job,
to find out what I could.

12:27.514 --> 12:30.115
-For who?
-Brian.

12:30.717 --> 12:34.219
Brian sent me. You scare him.

12:34.221 --> 12:35.687
He thinks you're
gonna cut him out,

12:35.689 --> 12:36.421
but he can't be
a man about it,

12:36.423 --> 12:41.359
so he's got me looking in
on how you move
the stuff coming in.

12:45.332 --> 12:47.298
So you his old lady now?

12:49.035 --> 12:53.171
I let him ball me.
Keeps him housebroken.

12:53.340 --> 12:56.574
Way he's built down there,
I barely notice.

12:57.310 --> 12:58.810
(CHUCKLES)

13:09.222 --> 13:11.189
Do you ever blink?

13:11.792 --> 13:13.892
You got eyes like a doll.

13:14.494 --> 13:16.094
I'll say this, doll eyes.

13:16.096 --> 13:18.263
You damn sure ain't here
'cause you can cook.

13:18.265 --> 13:21.199
(CHUCKLES) I had better
sandwiches in the joint.

13:22.502 --> 13:24.269
Then go back.

13:24.271 --> 13:24.702
Ow! (GROANING)

13:24.704 --> 13:27.872
Damn, Charlie!
You let these bitches
talk to you like this?

13:27.874 --> 13:30.041
I must have came
at the right time.

13:30.043 --> 13:32.110
-Charlie! Get off me!
-Charlie!

13:32.112 --> 13:34.045
Charlie ain't gonna do...

13:34.047 --> 13:35.380
RALPH: Charlie!

13:35.382 --> 13:35.747
Charlie!

13:35.749 --> 13:38.149
Why you hitting yourself, huh?
Why you hitting yourself?

13:38.151 --> 13:39.417
-Charlie!
-Why you hitting yourself?

13:39.419 --> 13:42.053
Why you hitting yourself?
What? You used to love that.

13:42.055 --> 13:43.822
-Charlie!
-(MOCKING) Charlie!

13:43.824 --> 13:45.056
-Charlie!
-Charlie!

13:45.058 --> 13:47.058
-Charlie!
-Charlie!

13:47.060 --> 13:48.560
BRIAN: Hey!

13:50.163 --> 13:52.030
What the hell is going on?

13:53.567 --> 13:55.633
I think she wants
you to let her go.

13:55.635 --> 13:57.569
I think I don't give a damn.

13:57.571 --> 14:00.071
Yeah,
well, I think you should.

14:00.340 --> 14:01.806
(SADIE PANTING)

14:04.544 --> 14:06.311
RALPH: What is this, Charlie?

14:06.313 --> 14:11.149
I'm just horsing around,
and this man want
to get serious.

14:12.319 --> 14:14.953
Well, I'm seriously
here, Charlie.

14:15.555 --> 14:20.792
And seriously,
(WHISPERS)
I ain't going nowhere.

14:26.833 --> 14:28.066
(SPITS)

14:33.573 --> 14:37.809
NEWSCASTER: <i> It's been</i>
<i> confirmed that during what had</i>
<i> been a negotiated cease-fire</i>

14:37.811 --> 14:39.577
<i> during the new</i>
<i> year holiday of Tet,</i>

14:39.579 --> 14:43.681
<i> the Viet Cong have</i>
<i> attacked the American</i>
<i> Embassy in Vietnam</i>

14:43.683 --> 14:45.683
<i> along with reports</i>
<i> of attacks in five</i>

14:45.685 --> 14:47.252
<i> provincial South</i>
<i> Vietnamese capitals.</i>

14:47.254 --> 14:49.621
<i> U.S. Forces seem</i>
<i> to have been caught</i>
<i> completely by surprise.</i>

14:49.623 --> 14:53.358
MEG: (ON RADIO)
<i> Six-William-Nine.</i>
<i> Six-William-Nine.</i>

14:53.627 --> 14:55.627
Six-William-Nine. Speak, Meg.

14:55.629 --> 14:58.263
Hey, Sam.
Patching in a call for you.

14:58.265 --> 14:59.197
<i> It's Officer Shafe.</i>

14:59.199 --> 15:03.534
BRIAN: <i> There's a Bleu Room</i>
<i> in Culver City on Pico.</i>

15:03.536 --> 15:05.970
Well played, young buck.

15:05.972 --> 15:08.840
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
-(SIRENS WAILING)

15:13.013 --> 15:14.112
Coffee?

15:14.114 --> 15:16.114
I'm hoping to get to bed soon.

15:16.349 --> 15:17.882
Me, too.

15:18.418 --> 15:19.951
A little up, a little down.

15:19.953 --> 15:22.487
I forget who I'm
breakfasting with.

15:23.023 --> 15:26.324
So, big surprise,
no Roy, no blonde quiff.

15:26.326 --> 15:29.093
They say if they'd been here,
where they might be now?

15:29.095 --> 15:31.296
No. Of course,
they were
falling over themselves

15:31.298 --> 15:33.998
to see which
they could be first,
courteous or helpful.

15:34.000 --> 15:38.369
If you had to cut
one out of the herd,
have a chat with, who'd it be?

15:38.371 --> 15:41.272
That big ugly fat
monster right there?

15:41.374 --> 15:42.006
You're that ugly,

15:42.008 --> 15:43.975
you've been
fighting your whole life.

15:43.977 --> 15:45.443
And not the little
stubby one, either.

15:45.445 --> 15:46.444
SAM: No, too much to prove.

15:46.446 --> 15:50.014
I'm in no mood
for a short man,
not tonight.

15:50.450 --> 15:52.317
-SAM: Eh, the pretty one.
-This a problem?

15:52.319 --> 15:53.785
-Am I right?
-MAN: Yes, we got a problem.

15:53.787 --> 15:55.586
-Thor.
-Just take that badge off.

15:55.588 --> 15:58.656
I like you, Sam,
but one thing you are not

15:58.658 --> 16:02.293
is a nice guy,
not even a little.

16:14.741 --> 16:19.243
Ooh. Damn.
You are really good-looking.

16:19.946 --> 16:23.114
I hope you don't
mind my saying,
but you've got great skin.

16:23.116 --> 16:24.916
-Doesn't he, Sarge?
-Very supple.

16:24.918 --> 16:28.953
Supple, yeah.
Smooth, tight, taut.

16:28.955 --> 16:30.488
It's taut, really, isn't it?

16:30.490 --> 16:32.724
I bet the girls
must just pile up

16:32.726 --> 16:34.726
outside your door
like snow banks, huh?

16:34.728 --> 16:39.797
I'm looking for Roy Kovic,
and nobody ever needs
to know you told me.

16:40.367 --> 16:41.766
I ain't telling you, man.

16:41.768 --> 16:42.400
Let me ask you, then,

16:42.402 --> 16:44.836
'cause the Sarge and I
aren't getting any younger,

16:44.838 --> 16:47.705
you think it's too late for us
to start moisturizing?

16:47.707 --> 16:49.073
You know,
a little cocoa butter

16:49.075 --> 16:49.974
before bed?
Is that your secret?

16:49.976 --> 16:54.212
Man, I don't know
what you're on,
but kiss my ass.

16:54.447 --> 16:56.214
(LAUGHS)

16:56.549 --> 16:57.682
Sarge.

16:57.684 --> 16:59.250
(GROANING)

17:03.923 --> 17:06.357
No, no, no. Please, come on.

17:06.359 --> 17:08.226
(YELLING)

17:08.228 --> 17:09.861
Venice. He's in Venice.
He's in Venice.

17:09.863 --> 17:11.429
Big town. Big town.

17:11.431 --> 17:13.231
(GROANS)

17:13.233 --> 17:14.532
San Juan Avenue.

17:14.534 --> 17:16.701
-(YELPING)
-Address?

17:16.703 --> 17:18.102
(PANTING)

17:18.104 --> 17:20.238
1501! 1501!

17:20.240 --> 17:21.372
Huh?

17:21.374 --> 17:22.640
1501!

17:22.642 --> 17:25.009
(GROANING)

17:26.980 --> 17:28.212
(GRUNTS)

17:31.284 --> 17:32.784
<i> Buon Appetito.</i>

17:50.737 --> 17:52.937
(PHONE RINGING)

17:57.777 --> 17:59.177
Hello?

17:59.379 --> 18:00.845
KEN: <i> Grace?</i>

18:01.181 --> 18:02.513
Ken?

18:03.783 --> 18:05.616
Please just listen.

18:06.419 --> 18:07.452
I knew that you'd be there.

18:07.454 --> 18:10.188
I'm not mad.
I don't want to fight.

18:10.356 --> 18:14.258
<i> I just want to tell you...</i>

18:15.295 --> 18:17.261
GRACE: <i> Ken, where are you?</i>

18:17.263 --> 18:18.830
Home.

18:20.867 --> 18:23.668
That's what we
still call it, right?

18:24.104 --> 18:26.604
I wish you could
see the sunrise.

18:27.207 --> 18:28.239
<i> It's so beautiful.</i>

18:28.241 --> 18:29.807
Ken, I can't
really talk right now.

18:29.809 --> 18:31.609
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

18:32.946 --> 18:34.679
<i> I'm so sorry.</i>

18:35.348 --> 18:37.248
<i> The mess of our lives.</i>

18:39.519 --> 18:40.885
It's me. It's all me,

18:40.887 --> 18:43.921
and I can't clean it up.

18:47.227 --> 18:50.428
I'm tired. I'm just so...

18:55.902 --> 18:57.802
I did love you.

18:59.038 --> 19:03.674
And Emma, our sweet girl.

19:06.012 --> 19:08.312
What we did to her.

19:10.650 --> 19:12.583
God forgive us both.

19:13.720 --> 19:14.785
<i> Ken.</i>

19:14.787 --> 19:16.354
(PHONE DISCONNECTS)

19:45.852 --> 19:47.752
(PHONE RINGING)

19:58.798 --> 20:01.199
(PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)

20:01.201 --> 20:02.567
(GUN CLICKS)

20:03.503 --> 20:05.002
GRACE: Hello?

20:05.238 --> 20:08.039
What? No, I...

20:08.041 --> 20:10.007
Oh, my God, when?

20:10.310 --> 20:11.676
I don't know.

20:12.545 --> 20:14.045
Ken?

20:14.247 --> 20:17.281
It's Betty Banyin.
Hal's been shot.

20:17.817 --> 20:20.151
The doctors say
he's gonna die.

20:49.682 --> 20:50.815
SAM: Hi.

20:50.817 --> 20:52.883
Oh, yeah, come on in, Officer.

20:52.885 --> 20:55.519
Where were you last
Tuesday night, Roy?

20:55.521 --> 20:58.556
Oh. I couldn't say. Why?

20:59.859 --> 21:01.959
Assume the position.

21:02.362 --> 21:05.596
Study the wall.
There's gonna be a quiz.

21:05.598 --> 21:06.364
(ROY SIGHS)

21:06.366 --> 21:08.299
Look, man,
what is all this about?

21:08.301 --> 21:10.601
I told you.
Last Tuesday night.

21:10.603 --> 21:12.637
WOMAN: He was with me.

21:19.078 --> 21:19.510
Who are you?

21:19.512 --> 21:23.648
Just somebody who
can say for sure
that Roy was with me.

21:24.284 --> 21:25.716
See some ID, miss?

21:25.718 --> 21:26.951
Come on.

21:43.403 --> 21:44.702
This your new girlfriend, Roy?

21:44.704 --> 21:46.270
Yeah, but I know
you're gonna want proof,

21:46.272 --> 21:49.573
so why don't you
show him that corsage
I bought you, honey?

21:49.575 --> 21:50.708
I'm turning over
a new leaf, Officer.

21:50.710 --> 21:54.879
This could be the last time
that the law comes knocking.

21:56.849 --> 22:00.051
Yeah,
she is just what you need.

22:09.962 --> 22:10.995
Wow.

22:10.997 --> 22:13.064
Charmain going deep.

22:14.634 --> 22:15.833
Is there
anything we should do?

22:15.835 --> 22:17.535
Besides spending
all night trying to

22:17.537 --> 22:19.503
rescue a cop that
doesn't need rescuing?

22:19.505 --> 22:20.137
No, I think we're good.

22:20.139 --> 22:23.374
Sam, I never noticed,
but you're looking
a little bloated.

22:24.177 --> 22:26.310
